textDelta: The most common naturally-occurring form in which silicon is found is in the form of silicon dioxide. This is a white, powdery material that is found in the earth's crust. Silicon dioxide is a good conductor of electricity and can be used to make electronic components and photovoltaic cells.
What form is silicon usually found in? Silicon is usually found in the form of small, crystalline grains.
